<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5979] ant release target creates a release.properties that has conflicting line endings so automatic checkin fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5979</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ant release target  on Windows  creates release.properties with inconsistent line endings that prevent checkin.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This may be a configuration issue.  I have *.properties = svn:eol-style=native which I think is correct but I could not diff or checkin the file until I removed the dos line endings.  There are similar issues with the release notes but because they are not checked in as part of the a script we document how to fix them up.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
